.Dd June 26, 2026
.Dt PSCAN 8
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm pscan
.Nd fast asynchronous TCP SYN and UDP port scanner
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl 46u
.Op Fl I Ar iface
.Op Fl p Ar ports
.Op Fl W Ar timeout
.Ar destination
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility is a fast port scanner that uses raw sockets to asynchronously discover open ports on a target host.
By default, it performs a TCP SYN scan, waiting for SYN-ACK responses.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl 4
Use IPv4 only.
.It Fl 6
Use IPv6 only.
.It Fl I Ar iface
Bind to a specific interface or source IP address.
.It Fl p Ar ports
Specify the port range to scan. Can be a single port (e.g., 80) or a range (e.g., 1-1024).
.It Fl u
Perform a UDP scan instead of a TCP SYN scan. It sends empty datagrams and relies on ICMP Port Unreachable responses to filter out closed ports.
.It Fl W Ar timeout
Time to wait for a response, in seconds.
.El
.Sh AUTHORS
